char array - 2d
char arr[3][4]={
  {'a','b','c'},
  {'d','e','f'},
  {'g','h','i'}
  };
  cout<<arr[0][0];//a b c d e f g ...... till we get null.
  to tackle this problem we use 2 methords
  in first one we use 
  {
  {'a','b','c','\0'},
  {'d','e','f','\0'},
  {'g','h','i','\0'}
  }
  {
  "abcd",
  "efgh",
